Date	: 25/02/04

To Install,

extract the files to 
C:\Program Files\Valve\Steam\SteamApps\STEAM@USERID\
counter-strike source\cstrike\maps

Scenario.

International terrorists have stowed away on a cruise ship
Late one evening the break cover with the intention sinking
the ship while it is far off-shore.

Tips

Site A is at the very rear of the ship behind the last row of
benches

Site B is in the control tower accesible via the escape ladder
or elevator from the dining room.

You can climb up into the helicopter but be careful the ropes
are blowing in the wind and can be hard to climb.

In the engine room there are 3 switches that control the lights
on the 3 decks of the ship, use these to plunge the ship into
darkness and use the shadows.

If you get stuck in the eleveator to the control room there is
a flap in the roof to escape.

There is a horn in the control tower and though fun will alert
everyone to your location.

  Ten Levels In One - Defuse Scenario

Like your favorite ice-cream stacked high 
on a hot summers day, this level blends 
10 unique environments in a vertical
pancake to form one cohesive and digestible 
piece of deliciousness. Enjoy!
 
Counter-Terrorists: 
Defend the water plant(A), underground(B), 
and dock(C) from terrorists. Prevent the 
terrorists from planting the device and 
succeeding with their objective. 

Terrorists: 
Navigate your way up to the upper levels 
and destroy the objectives at the (C)docks, 
(B)underground, or (A)water plant. Always be 
aware of what's above you!
 
Other Notes: There are three objective sites
in this level. All grouped together and
labeled A, B, and C

De_CrookCounty is massive in size. The unzipped .bsp file is 80mb in size, while the map is over 4 city blocks in size. Terrorists start inside the jail cells of the police station and manage to escape, while the Counter-Terrorists start off approximately 3 blocks away from Crook County PD. There's quite a lot of routes both teams can take, but ultimately the main objective of both teams is to reach either Ammunition (Site A) or the 5 story tenement building (Site B). The Terrorists can plant the bomb on any floor of the gun shop, and floors 2-5 of the tenement building which causes frustration as the CT's search room-to-room and floor-to-floor for the hidden bomb.

Its recommended that servers which run this map disable AWP's and Auto sniper rifles, as they tend to be cheap to those who tend to run down the street without thinking. Limiting the AWP to one or two people per team is a better idea, though. Just make sure to use some stealth by hiding in the shadows as it works wonders.
